# Trellis-development-only files. `export-ignore` keeps them OUT of `git archive`,
# GitHub's "Download ZIP", and release tarballs — so anyone who DOWNLOADS Trellis
# gets a clean scaffold, not the whole dev repo. (Contributors who `git clone` still
# get everything.) `trellis new <name>` applies the same curation to scaffolded projects.
WORKPLAN.md export-ignore
.gitattributes export-ignore
